HEADWORD: Turnicimorphae
<hw>Tur`ni*ci*mor"phae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pr. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Turnix</er>, and <er>-morphous</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of birds including <gen>Turnix</gen>
and allied genera, resembling quails in appearance but differing from
them anatomically.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

